[SN]TITLE[SN]
One-armed pilot passes test with home-made prosthetic limb

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A one-armed man from Leeds has passed his pilot's exam using a home-made prosthetic limb.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Media playback is unsupported on your device
12 July 2015 Last updated at 17:44 BST
Steve Robinson lost his arm in an accident but was determined to realise his dream of becoming a pilot.
He said two previous prosthetic arms had not worked properly, so he made his own.
"I thought, 'Am I going to give in? No way - I'll make my own prosthetic arm'," he said.
